[2] Brazil (Federal District, Goias)
Date: Thu 2 Sep 2004
From: Tatyane Leandro de Sousa <tatyane.sousa@anvisa.gov.br>
Via: LISAS <lisas@lisas.org.br>
Source: Jornal de Brasilia, Thu 2 Sep 2004 [in Portuguese, summarized by
Mod.JW, edited]
<http://www.jornaldebrasilia.com.br/WebComponents/conteudo.php?Ac=NotEdi&IdEdicao=538&IdEditoria=10&IdNoticia=5>


Brazil: 24 Confirmed Cases and 10 Deaths in Federal District
--------------------------------------------------
The number of confirmed cases of hantavirus infection in the Federal
District of Brazil rose to 24, including 10 deaths. Outside the Federal
District, there have been 8 cases, including 4 deaths. One was a
41-year-old farmer who lived in the town of Luziania, Goias state [which
borders the Federal District], and who died 25 days ago, only 12 hours
after the first symptoms appeared. Another was in Planaltina de Goias, and
has been discharged from hospital.

The lab diagnosis was made by the Institute Adolfo Lutz of Sao Paulo.

